EIGHTY suspects will appear in the Krugersdorp Magistrates Court on Monday, 1 August. The suspect were bust at the weekend after the police specialised units swooped at West Village in Krugersdorp following the gang rape of eight women on Thursday, 28 July. The eight victims, most of them from Alexandra, east Joburg, were part of a filming crew that was in the area to shoot a music video. At the moment it’s not known if the 20 suspects accused of raping the eight women are among the 80 arrested men. ALSO READ: Siblings gang rape horror Police said they’ll be able to link them through DNA. The results will be available by the end of this week. Most of the suspects were arrested for various crimes, including illegal mining and being in the country illegally. On Sunday, 31 July, the victims were locked in a meeting with Police Minister Bheki Cele and the team of detectives who are working on the case. The victims are undergoing counselling organised by the police. The police said they wanted them to focus on their psychological well-being before they could get their detailed statements on what really happened.